OL,5, At 2:15am on Christmas morning last    
OL,6, year, Ruth Perry woke and wrote down   
OL,7, her thoughts while her two teenage     
OL,8, daughters and husband slept.           
OL,10,F"I.N.A.D.E.Q.U.A.T.E keeps flashing    
OL,11,Fbehind my eyes."                       
OL,13,FShe had been head teacher at Caversham 
OL,14,FPrimary School, in Reading, for 13     
OL,15,Fyears - the school had always been     
OL,16,Fjudged as "outstanding".               
OL,18,FThe previous month, inspectors had     
OL,19,Fvisited, and Ruth knew they were going 
OL,20,Fto downgrade her school to the lowest  
